          <msContents class="lemmatic">
            <summary>Dār al-Kutub, MS 4751 tibb is a modern copy (<date calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1942" notBefore="1942">1942</date>) of Damascus, Maktabat
                            al-Asad 3152. This codex consists of two parts.</summary>
            <msItem n="1">
              <locus from="1" to="164">pp. 1-164</locus>
              <author>
                <name type="person" key="nr89011237" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/81975562" subtype="aut">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">ʿAbd al-Laṭīf al-Baǧdādī‏</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">عبد اللطيف البغدادي</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="ara">كتاب تقدمة المعرفة لبقراط وتفسيره للشيخ الإمام
                                الفاضل أبي الفضل عبد اللطيف بن يوسف بن محمد البغدادي </title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Hippocrates' Prognostics and Abd Latif
                                Baghdadi's Commentary on it.</title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="alt">Kitāb Taqdimat al-Maʿrifa wa tafsīruh
                                li l-šayḫ al-ʾimām al-fāḍil ʿAbi l-Faḍl ʿAbd al-Laṭīf ...
                                al-Baǧdādī</title>
              <note>This is a copy of Hippocrates' Prognostics and ʿAbd al-Laṭīf
                                al-Baǧdādī's Commentary on it. </note>
              <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
            </msItem>
            <msItem n="2">
              <locus from="1" to="168"> pp. 1-168</locus>
              <author>
                <name type="person" key="n 2008049541" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" subtype="aut">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Commentary on Hippocratic
                                Aphorisms</title>
              <title xml:lang="ara">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="alt">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
              <note> This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction
                                begins on <locus>p. 2</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as
                                follows: Bk1: p. 4; Bk2: p. 34; Bk3: p. 84; Bk4: p. 119 (in p. 145,
                                line 14, iv. 14 ends). Afterwards, the copy is missing several
                                pages: p. 145, line 14: middle of i.4-16 p. 154: vii. 44 p. 155: vi.
                                35 p. 159: vii. 50-end.
                                It is a copy of Ibn ʾAbī Ṣādiq's commentary although on the front page, this copy is entitled "The second part of Hippocrates' Prognostics and ʿAbd al-Laṭīf
                                al-Baǧdādī's Commentary on it".
                            </note>
              <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
            </msItem>
